README.md
     1‚Üí# color
     3‚ÜíColor lets you use colorized outputs in terms of [ANSI Escape
     4‚ÜíCodes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#Colors) in Go (Golang). It
     5‚Üíhas support for Windows too! The API can be used in several ways, pick one that
     6‚Üísuits you.
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí![Color](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/438920/96832689-03b3e000-13f4-11eb-9803-46f4c4de3406.jpg)
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí## Install
    12‚Üí```
    13‚Üígo get github.com/fatih/color
    14‚Üí```
    15‚Üí
    16‚Üí## Examples
    18‚Üí### Standard colors ‚Ä¶
    33‚Üí### RGB colors ‚Ä¶
    45‚Üí### Mix and reuse colors ‚Ä¶
    71‚Üí### Use your own output (io.Writer) ‚Ä¶
    81‚Üí### Custom print functions (PrintFunc) ‚Ä¶
    94‚Üí### Custom fprint functions (FprintFunc) ‚Ä¶
   105‚Üí### Insert into noncolor strings (SprintFunc) ‚Ä¶
   124‚Üí### Plug into existing code ‚Ä¶
   142‚Üí### Disable/Enable color ‚Ä¶
   177‚Üí## GitHub Actions
   179‚ÜíTo output color in GitHub Actions (or other CI systems that support ANSI colors), make sure to set `color.NoColor = false` so that it bypasses the check for non-tty output streams. 
   180‚Üí
